					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That's a better explanation. ca65 will let you define .word/.bytes or whatever in a RAM segment, but it won't actually place anything there for you.<br /><br />I assume (untested) you could define your ZP segment load as:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">MEMORY<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;ZP:&nbsp; start =&nbsp; &nbsp; $0, size =&nbsp; &nbsp;$100,&nbsp; type = rw,&nbsp; define = yes, fillval = $AA;<br />}<br /></div> <br />And then:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">.segment &quot;ZEROPAGE&quot;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; bar: .word $AA&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; matches what the fillval for ZP is suppose to be.<br /></div><br /><br />If the value doesn't match, you'll get a linker error.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

